  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Bridging the Gaps 2 - PWUD project Vietnam</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In close collaboration with a local partner in Vietnam and SOA AIDS the Netherlands we assessed the meth-use, risk taking behaviours and options for service delivery in Ho Chi Mihn City in Vietnam. Based on this mapping exercise we intend to expand harm reduction services to address the needs of meth users</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">People who Use Drugs</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Vietnam has seen a rise in the use of chrystal-methamphetamine in recent years. Harm reduction services in Vietnam are oriented towards heroin users who inject their drug. A local partner of the sex worker project under BtG2 flagged a concern around the rise in meth-use among sex workers, but also among the general population</narrative>
  </description>
